In a paradigm previously described [23], participants were presented with three different tasks randomized across six blocks, with two blocks per task (
Figure 2
). There were two WM tasks: Interrupting Stimulus (IS), and No Interference (NI). A third task instructed participants to passively view the stimuli (PV). At T1, participants completed another WM task, Distracting Stimulus (DS), which was not completed at T2 because of experimental time constraints.Results are not discussed here.
